49// TODO(mallinath) - Move these to a common place.
50inline bool IsTurnChannelData(uint16_t msg_type) {
51 // The first two bits of a channel data message are 0b01.
52 return ((msg_type & 0xC000) == 0x4000);
53}

60// Encapsulates a TURN permission.
61// The object is created when a create permission request is received by an
62// allocation, and self-deletes when its lifetime timer expires.
63class TurnServerAllocation::Permission : public rtc::MessageHandlerAutoCleanup {
64 public:
65 Permission(rtc::Thread* thread, const rtc::IPAddress& peer);
66 ~Permission() override;
67
68 const rtc::IPAddress& peer() const { return peer_; }
69 void Refresh();
70
71 sigslot::signal1<Permission*> SignalDestroyed;
72
73 private:
74 void OnMessage(rtc::Message* msg) override;
75
76 rtc::Thread* thread_;
77 rtc::IPAddress peer_;
78};

80// Encapsulates a TURN channel binding.
81// The object is created when a channel bind request is received by an
82// allocation, and self-deletes when its lifetime timer expires.
83class TurnServerAllocation::Channel : public rtc::MessageHandlerAutoCleanup {
84 public:
85 Channel(rtc::Thread* thread, int id, const rtc::SocketAddress& peer);
86 ~Channel() override;
87
88 int id() const { return id_; }
89 const rtc::SocketAddress& peer() const { return peer_; }
90 void Refresh();
91
92 sigslot::signal1<Channel*> SignalDestroyed;
93
94 private:
95 void OnMessage(rtc::Message* msg) override;
96
97 rtc::Thread* thread_;
98 int id_;
99 rtc::SocketAddress peer_;
100};

102static bool InitResponse(const StunMessage* req, StunMessage* resp) {
103 int resp_type = (req) ? GetStunSuccessResponseType(req->type()) : -1;
104 if (resp_type == -1)
105 return false;
106 resp->SetType(resp_type);
107 resp->SetTransactionID(req->transaction_id());
108 return true;
109}
110
111static bool InitErrorResponse(const StunMessage* req,
112 int code,
113 const std::string& reason,
114 StunMessage* resp) {
115 int resp_type = (req) ? GetStunErrorResponseType(req->type()) : -1;
116 if (resp_type == -1)
117 return false;
118 resp->SetType(resp_type);
119 resp->SetTransactionID(req->transaction_id());
120 resp->AddAttribute(std::make_unique<cricket::StunErrorCodeAttribute>(
121 STUN_ATTR_ERROR_CODE, code, reason));
122 return true;
123}

125TurnServer::TurnServer(rtc::Thread* thread)
126 : thread_(thread),
127 nonce_key_(rtc::CreateRandomString(kNonceKeySize)),
128 auth_hook_(NULL),
129 redirect_hook_(NULL),
130 enable_otu_nonce_(false) {}

132TurnServer::~TurnServer() {
133 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
134 for (InternalSocketMap::iterator it = server_sockets_.begin();
135 it != server_sockets_.end(); ++it) {
136 rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket = it->first;
137 delete socket;
138 }
139
140 for (ServerSocketMap::iterator it = server_listen_sockets_.begin();
141 it != server_listen_sockets_.end(); ++it) {
142 rtc::AsyncSocket* socket = it->first;
143 delete socket;
144 }
145}
146
147void TurnServer::AddInternalSocket(rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket,
148 ProtocolType proto) {
149 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
150 RTC_DCHECK(server_sockets_.end() == server_sockets_.find(socket));
151 server_sockets_[socket] = proto;
152 socket->SignalReadPacket.connect(this, &TurnServer::OnInternalPacket);
153}
154
155void TurnServer::AddInternalServerSocket(rtc::AsyncSocket* socket,
156 ProtocolType proto) {
157 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
158 RTC_DCHECK(server_listen_sockets_.end() ==
159 server_listen_sockets_.find(socket));
160 server_listen_sockets_[socket] = proto;
161 socket->SignalReadEvent.connect(this, &TurnServer::OnNewInternalConnection);
162}

168 external_socket_factory_.reset(factory);

172void TurnServer::OnNewInternalConnection(rtc::AsyncSocket* socket) {
173 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
174 RTC_DCHECK(server_listen_sockets_.find(socket) !=
175 server_listen_sockets_.end());
176 AcceptConnection(socket);
177}
178
179void TurnServer::AcceptConnection(rtc::AsyncSocket* server_socket) {
180 // Check if someone is trying to connect to us.
181 rtc::SocketAddress accept_addr;
182 rtc::AsyncSocket* accepted_socket = server_socket->Accept(&accept_addr);
183 if (accepted_socket != NULL) {
184 ProtocolType proto = server_listen_sockets_[server_socket];
185 cricket::AsyncStunTCPSocket* tcp_socket =
186 new cricket::AsyncStunTCPSocket(accepted_socket, false);
187
188 tcp_socket->SignalClose.connect(this, &TurnServer::OnInternalSocketClose);
189 // Finally add the socket so it can start communicating with the client.
190 AddInternalSocket(tcp_socket, proto);
191 }
192}
193
194void TurnServer::OnInternalSocketClose(rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket,
195 int err) {
196 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
197 DestroyInternalSocket(socket);
198}
199
200void TurnServer::OnInternalPacket(rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket,
201 const char* data,
202 size_t size,
203 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr,
204 const int64_t& /* packet_time_us */) {
205 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
206 // Fail if the packet is too small to even contain a channel header.
207 if (size < TURN_CHANNEL_HEADER_SIZE) {
208 return;
209 }
210 InternalSocketMap::iterator iter = server_sockets_.find(socket);
211 RTC_DCHECK(iter != server_sockets_.end());
212 TurnServerConnection conn(addr, iter->second, socket);
213 uint16_t msg_type = rtc::GetBE16(data);
214 if (!IsTurnChannelData(msg_type)) {
215 // This is a STUN message.
216 HandleStunMessage(&conn, data, size);
217 } else {
218 // This is a channel message; let the allocation handle it.
219 TurnServerAllocation* allocation = FindAllocation(&conn);
220 if (allocation) {
221 allocation->HandleChannelData(data, size);
222 }
223 if (stun_message_observer_ != nullptr) {
224 stun_message_observer_->ReceivedChannelData(data, size);
225 }
226 }
227}
228
229void TurnServer::HandleStunMessage(TurnServerConnection* conn,
230 const char* data,
231 size_t size) {
232 TurnMessage msg;
233 rtc::ByteBufferReader buf(data, size);
234 if (!msg.Read(&buf) || (buf.Length() > 0)) {
235 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Received invalid STUN message";
236 return;
237 }
238
239 if (stun_message_observer_ != nullptr) {
240 stun_message_observer_->ReceivedMessage(&msg);
241 }
242
243 // If it's a STUN binding request, handle that specially.
244 if (msg.type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST) {
245 HandleBindingRequest(conn, &msg);
246 return;
247 }
248
249 if (redirect_hook_ != NULL && msg.type() == STUN_ALLOCATE_REQUEST) {
250 rtc::SocketAddress address;
251 if (redirect_hook_->ShouldRedirect(conn->src(), &address)) {
252 SendErrorResponseWithAlternateServer(conn, &msg, address);
253 return;
254 }
255 }
256
257 // Look up the key that we'll use to validate the M-I. If we have an
258 // existing allocation, the key will already be cached.
259 TurnServerAllocation* allocation = FindAllocation(conn);
260 std::string key;
261 if (!allocation) {
262 GetKey(&msg, &key);
263 } else {
264 key = allocation->key();
265 }
266
267 // Ensure the message is authorized; only needed for requests.
268 if (IsStunRequestType(msg.type())) {
269 if (!CheckAuthorization(conn, &msg, data, size, key)) {
270 return;
271 }
272 }
273
274 if (!allocation && msg.type() == STUN_ALLOCATE_REQUEST) {
275 HandleAllocateRequest(conn, &msg, key);
276 } else if (allocation &&
277 (msg.type() != STUN_ALLOCATE_REQUEST ||
278 msg.transaction_id() == allocation->transaction_id())) {
279 // This is a non-allocate request, or a retransmit of an allocate.
280 // Check that the username matches the previous username used.
281 if (IsStunRequestType(msg.type()) &&
282 msg.GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_USERNAME)->GetString() !=
283 allocation->username()) {
284 SendErrorResponse(conn, &msg, STUN_ERROR_WRONG_CREDENTIALS,
285 STUN_ERROR_REASON_WRONG_CREDENTIALS);
286 return;
287 }
288 allocation->HandleTurnMessage(&msg);
289 } else {
290 // Allocation mismatch.
291 SendErrorResponse(conn, &msg, STUN_ERROR_ALLOCATION_MISMATCH,
292 STUN_ERROR_REASON_ALLOCATION_MISMATCH);
293 }
294}
295
296bool TurnServer::GetKey(const StunMessage* msg, std::string* key) {
297 const StunByteStringAttribute* username_attr =
298 msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_USERNAME);
299 if (!username_attr) {
300 return false;
301 }
302
303 std::string username = username_attr->GetString();
304 return (auth_hook_ != NULL && auth_hook_->GetKey(username, realm_, key));
305}
306
307bool TurnServer::CheckAuthorization(TurnServerConnection* conn,
308 StunMessage* msg,
309 const char* data,
310 size_t size,
311 const std::string& key) {
312 // RFC 5389, 10.2.2.
313 RTC_DCHECK(IsStunRequestType(msg->type()));
314 const StunByteStringAttribute* mi_attr =
315 msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_MESSAGE_INTEGRITY);
316 const StunByteStringAttribute* username_attr =
317 msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_USERNAME);
318 const StunByteStringAttribute* realm_attr =
319 msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_REALM);
320 const StunByteStringAttribute* nonce_attr =
321 msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_NONCE);
322
323 // Fail if no MESSAGE_INTEGRITY.
324 if (!mi_attr) {
325 SendErrorResponseWithRealmAndNonce(conn, msg, STUN_ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED,
326 STUN_ERROR_REASON_UNAUTHORIZED);
327 return false;
328 }
329
330 // Fail if there is MESSAGE_INTEGRITY but no username, nonce, or realm.
331 if (!username_attr || !realm_attr || !nonce_attr) {
332 SendErrorResponse(conn, msg, STUN_ERROR_BAD_REQUEST,
333 STUN_ERROR_REASON_BAD_REQUEST);
334 return false;
335 }
336
337 // Fail if bad nonce.
338 if (!ValidateNonce(nonce_attr->GetString())) {
339 SendErrorResponseWithRealmAndNonce(conn, msg, STUN_ERROR_STALE_NONCE,
340 STUN_ERROR_REASON_STALE_NONCE);
341 return false;
342 }
343
344 // Fail if bad MESSAGE_INTEGRITY.
345 if (key.empty() || msg->ValidateMessageIntegrity(key) !=
346 StunMessage::IntegrityStatus::kIntegrityOk) {
347 SendErrorResponseWithRealmAndNonce(conn, msg, STUN_ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED,
348 STUN_ERROR_REASON_UNAUTHORIZED);
349 return false;
350 }
351
352 // Fail if one-time-use nonce feature is enabled.
353 TurnServerAllocation* allocation = FindAllocation(conn);
354 if (enable_otu_nonce_ && allocation &&
355 allocation->last_nonce() == nonce_attr->GetString()) {
356 SendErrorResponseWithRealmAndNonce(conn, msg, STUN_ERROR_STALE_NONCE,
357 STUN_ERROR_REASON_STALE_NONCE);
358 return false;
359 }
360
361 if (allocation) {
362 allocation->set_last_nonce(nonce_attr->GetString());
363 }
364 // Success.
365 return true;
366}
367
368void TurnServer::HandleBindingRequest(TurnServerConnection* conn,
369 const StunMessage* req) {
370 StunMessage response;
371 InitResponse(req, &response);
372
373 // Tell the user the address that we received their request from.
374 auto mapped_addr_attr = std::make_unique<StunXorAddressAttribute>(
375 STUN_ATTR_XOR_MAPPED_ADDRESS, conn->src());
376 response.AddAttribute(std::move(mapped_addr_attr));
377
378 SendStun(conn, &response);
379}
380
381void TurnServer::HandleAllocateRequest(TurnServerConnection* conn,
382 const TurnMessage* msg,
383 const std::string& key) {
384 // Check the parameters in the request.
385 const StunUInt32Attribute* transport_attr =
386 msg->GetUInt32(STUN_ATTR_REQUESTED_TRANSPORT);
387 if (!transport_attr) {
388 SendErrorResponse(conn, msg, STUN_ERROR_BAD_REQUEST,
389 STUN_ERROR_REASON_BAD_REQUEST);
390 return;
391 }
392
393 // Only UDP is supported right now.
394 int proto = transport_attr->value() >> 24;
395 if (proto != IPPROTO_UDP) {
396 SendErrorResponse(conn, msg, STUN_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_PROTOCOL,
397 STUN_ERROR_REASON_UNSUPPORTED_PROTOCOL);
398 return;
399 }
400
401 // Create the allocation and let it send the success response.
402 // If the actual socket allocation fails, send an internal error.
403 TurnServerAllocation* alloc = CreateAllocation(conn, proto, key);
404 if (alloc) {
405 alloc->HandleTurnMessage(msg);
406 } else {
407 SendErrorResponse(conn, msg, STUN_ERROR_SERVER_ERROR,
408 "Failed to allocate socket");
409 }
410}
411
412std::string TurnServer::GenerateNonce(int64_t now) const {
413 // Generate a nonce of the form hex(now + HMAC-MD5(nonce_key_, now))
414 std::string input(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(&now), sizeof(now));
415 std::string nonce = rtc::hex_encode(input.c_str(), input.size());
416 nonce += rtc::ComputeHmac(rtc::DIGEST_MD5, nonce_key_, input);
417 RTC_DCHECK(nonce.size() == kNonceSize);
418
419 return nonce;
420}
421
422bool TurnServer::ValidateNonce(const std::string& nonce) const {
423 // Check the size.
424 if (nonce.size() != kNonceSize) {
425 return false;
426 }
427
428 // Decode the timestamp.
429 int64_t then;
430 char* p = reinterpret_cast<char*>(&then);
431 size_t len =
432 rtc::hex_decode(p, sizeof(then), nonce.substr(0, sizeof(then) * 2));
433 if (len != sizeof(then)) {
434 return false;
435 }
436
437 // Verify the HMAC.
438 if (nonce.substr(sizeof(then) * 2) !=
439 rtc::ComputeHmac(rtc::DIGEST_MD5, nonce_key_,
440 std::string(p, sizeof(then)))) {
441 return false;
442 }
443
444 // Validate the timestamp.
445 return rtc::TimeMillis() - then < kNonceTimeout;
446}
447
448TurnServerAllocation* TurnServer::FindAllocation(TurnServerConnection* conn) {
449 AllocationMap::const_iterator it = allocations_.find(*conn);
450 return (it != allocations_.end()) ? it->second.get() : nullptr;
451}
452
453TurnServerAllocation* TurnServer::CreateAllocation(TurnServerConnection* conn,
454 int proto,
455 const std::string& key) {
456 rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* external_socket =
457 (external_socket_factory_)
458 ? external_socket_factory_->CreateUdpSocket(external_addr_, 0, 0)
459 : NULL;
460 if (!external_socket) {
461 return NULL;
462 }
463
464 // The Allocation takes ownership of the socket.
465 TurnServerAllocation* allocation =
466 new TurnServerAllocation(this, thread_, *conn, external_socket, key);
467 allocation->SignalDestroyed.connect(this, &TurnServer::OnAllocationDestroyed);
468 allocations_[*conn].reset(allocation);
469 return allocation;
470}
471
472void TurnServer::SendErrorResponse(TurnServerConnection* conn,
473 const StunMessage* req,
474 int code,
475 const std::string& reason) {
476 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
477 TurnMessage resp;
478 InitErrorResponse(req, code, reason, &resp);
479 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Sending error response, type=" << resp.type()
480 << ", code=" << code << ", reason=" << reason;
481 SendStun(conn, &resp);
482}
483
484void TurnServer::SendErrorResponseWithRealmAndNonce(TurnServerConnection* conn,
485 const StunMessage* msg,
486 int code,
487 const std::string& reason) {
488 TurnMessage resp;
489 InitErrorResponse(msg, code, reason, &resp);
490
491 int64_t timestamp = rtc::TimeMillis();
492 if (ts_for_next_nonce_) {
493 timestamp = ts_for_next_nonce_;
494 ts_for_next_nonce_ = 0;
495 }
496 resp.AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunByteStringAttribute>(
497 STUN_ATTR_NONCE, GenerateNonce(timestamp)));
498 resp.AddAttribute(
499 std::make_unique<StunByteStringAttribute>(STUN_ATTR_REALM, realm_));
500 SendStun(conn, &resp);
501}
502
503void TurnServer::SendErrorResponseWithAlternateServer(
504 TurnServerConnection* conn,
505 const StunMessage* msg,
506 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr) {
507 TurnMessage resp;
508 InitErrorResponse(msg, STUN_ERROR_TRY_ALTERNATE,
509 STUN_ERROR_REASON_TRY_ALTERNATE_SERVER, &resp);
510 resp.AddAttribute(
511 std::make_unique<StunAddressAttribute>(STUN_ATTR_ALTERNATE_SERVER, addr));
512 SendStun(conn, &resp);
513}
514
515void TurnServer::SendStun(TurnServerConnection* conn, StunMessage* msg) {
516 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
517 rtc::ByteBufferWriter buf;
518 // Add a SOFTWARE attribute if one is set.
519 if (!software_.empty()) {
520 msg->AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunByteStringAttribute>(
521 STUN_ATTR_SOFTWARE, software_));
522 }
523 msg->Write(&buf);
524 Send(conn, buf);
525}
526
527void TurnServer::Send(TurnServerConnection* conn,
528 const rtc::ByteBufferWriter& buf) {
529 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
530 rtc::PacketOptions options;
531 conn->socket()->SendTo(buf.Data(), buf.Length(), conn->src(), options);
532}
533
534void TurnServer::OnAllocationDestroyed(TurnServerAllocation* allocation) {
535 // Removing the internal socket if the connection is not udp.
536 rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket = allocation->conn()->socket();
537 InternalSocketMap::iterator iter = server_sockets_.find(socket);
538 // Skip if the socket serving this allocation is UDP, as this will be shared
539 // by all allocations.
540 // Note: We may not find a socket if it's a TCP socket that was closed, and
541 // the allocation is only now timing out.
542 if (iter != server_sockets_.end() && iter->second != cricket::PROTO_UDP) {
543 DestroyInternalSocket(socket);
544 }
545
546 AllocationMap::iterator it = allocations_.find(*(allocation->conn()));
547 if (it != allocations_.end()) {
548 it->second.release();
549 allocations_.erase(it);
550 }
551}
552
553void TurnServer::DestroyInternalSocket(rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket) {
554 InternalSocketMap::iterator iter = server_sockets_.find(socket);
555 if (iter != server_sockets_.end()) {
556 rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket = iter->first;
557 socket->SignalReadPacket.disconnect(this);
558 server_sockets_.erase(iter);
559 std::unique_ptr<rtc::AsyncPacketSocket> socket_to_delete =
560 absl::WrapUnique(socket);
561 // We must destroy the socket async to avoid invalidating the sigslot
562 // callback list iterator inside a sigslot callback. (In other words,
563 // deleting an object from within a callback from that object).
564 thread_->PostTask(webrtc::ToQueuedTask(
565 [socket_to_delete = std::move(socket_to_delete)] {}));
566 }
567}

569TurnServerConnection::TurnServerConnection(const rtc::SocketAddress& src,
570 ProtocolType proto,
571 rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket)
572 : src_(src),
573 dst_(socket->GetRemoteAddress()),
574 proto_(proto),
575 socket_(socket) {}
576
577bool TurnServerConnection::operator==(const TurnServerConnection& c) const {
578 return src_ == c.src_ && dst_ == c.dst_ && proto_ == c.proto_;
579}
580
581bool TurnServerConnection::operator<(const TurnServerConnection& c) const {
582 return std::tie(src_, dst_, proto_) < std::tie(c.src_, c.dst_, c.proto_);
583}

585std::string TurnServerConnection::ToString() const {
586 const char* const kProtos[] = {"unknown", "udp", "tcp", "ssltcp"};
587 rtc::StringBuilder ost;
588 ost << src_.ToSensitiveString() << "-" << dst_.ToSensitiveString() << ":"
589 << kProtos[proto_];
590 return ost.Release();
591}

606
607TurnServerAllocation::~TurnServerAllocation() {
608 for (ChannelList::iterator it = channels_.begin(); it != channels_.end();
609 ++it) {
610 delete *it;
611 }
612 for (PermissionList::iterator it = perms_.begin(); it != perms_.end(); ++it) {
613 delete *it;
614 }
615 thread_->Clear(this, MSG_ALLOCATION_TIMEOUT);
616 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Allocation destroyed";
617}

622 return ost.Release();
623}
624
625void TurnServerAllocation::HandleTurnMessage(const TurnMessage* msg) {
626 RTC_DCHECK(msg != NULL);
627 switch (msg->type()) {
628 case STUN_ALLOCATE_REQUEST:
629 HandleAllocateRequest(msg);
630 break;
631 case TURN_REFRESH_REQUEST:
632 HandleRefreshRequest(msg);
633 break;
634 case TURN_SEND_INDICATION:
635 HandleSendIndication(msg);
636 break;
637 case TURN_CREATE_PERMISSION_REQUEST:
638 HandleCreatePermissionRequest(msg);
639 break;
640 case TURN_CHANNEL_BIND_REQUEST:
641 HandleChannelBindRequest(msg);
642 break;
643 default:
644 // Not sure what to do with this, just eat it.
645 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << ToString()
646 << ": Invalid TURN message type received: "
647 << msg->type();
648 }
649}
650
651void TurnServerAllocation::HandleAllocateRequest(const TurnMessage* msg) {
652 // Copy the important info from the allocate request.
653 transaction_id_ = msg->transaction_id();
654 const StunByteStringAttribute* username_attr =
655 msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_USERNAME);
656 RTC_DCHECK(username_attr != NULL);
657 username_ = username_attr->GetString();
658 const StunByteStringAttribute* origin_attr =
659 msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_ORIGIN);
660 if (origin_attr) {
661 origin_ = origin_attr->GetString();
662 }
663
664 // Figure out the lifetime and start the allocation timer.
665 int lifetime_secs = ComputeLifetime(msg);
666 thread_->PostDelayed(RTC_FROM_HERE, lifetime_secs * 1000, this,
667 MSG_ALLOCATION_TIMEOUT);
668
669 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
670 << ": Created allocation with lifetime=" << lifetime_secs;
671
672 // We've already validated all the important bits; just send a response here.
673 TurnMessage response;
674 InitResponse(msg, &response);
675
676 auto mapped_addr_attr = std::make_unique<StunXorAddressAttribute>(
677 STUN_ATTR_XOR_MAPPED_ADDRESS, conn_.src());
678 auto relayed_addr_attr = std::make_unique<StunXorAddressAttribute>(
679 STUN_ATTR_XOR_RELAYED_ADDRESS, external_socket_->GetLocalAddress());
680 auto lifetime_attr =
681 std::make_unique<StunUInt32Attribute>(STUN_ATTR_LIFETIME, lifetime_secs);
682 response.AddAttribute(std::move(mapped_addr_attr));
683 response.AddAttribute(std::move(relayed_addr_attr));
684 response.AddAttribute(std::move(lifetime_attr));
685
686 SendResponse(&response);
687}
688
689void TurnServerAllocation::HandleRefreshRequest(const TurnMessage* msg) {
690 // Figure out the new lifetime.
691 int lifetime_secs = ComputeLifetime(msg);
692
693 // Reset the expiration timer.
694 thread_->Clear(this, MSG_ALLOCATION_TIMEOUT);
695 thread_->PostDelayed(RTC_FROM_HERE, lifetime_secs * 1000, this,
696 MSG_ALLOCATION_TIMEOUT);
697
698 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
699 << ": Refreshed allocation, lifetime=" << lifetime_secs;
700
701 // Send a success response with a LIFETIME attribute.
702 TurnMessage response;
703 InitResponse(msg, &response);
704
705 auto lifetime_attr =
706 std::make_unique<StunUInt32Attribute>(STUN_ATTR_LIFETIME, lifetime_secs);
707 response.AddAttribute(std::move(lifetime_attr));
708
709 SendResponse(&response);
710}
711
712void TurnServerAllocation::HandleSendIndication(const TurnMessage* msg) {
713 // Check mandatory attributes.
714 const StunByteStringAttribute* data_attr = msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_DATA);
715 const StunAddressAttribute* peer_attr =
716 msg->GetAddress(STUN_ATTR_XOR_PEER_ADDRESS);
717 if (!data_attr || !peer_attr) {
718 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << ToString() << ": Received invalid send indication";
719 return;
720 }
721
722 // If a permission exists, send the data on to the peer.
723 if (HasPermission(peer_attr->GetAddress().ipaddr())) {
724 SendExternal(data_attr->bytes(), data_attr->length(),
725 peer_attr->GetAddress());
726 } else {
727 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << ToString()
728 << ": Received send indication without permission"
729 " peer="
730 << peer_attr->GetAddress().ToSensitiveString();
731 }
732}
733
734void TurnServerAllocation::HandleCreatePermissionRequest(
735 const TurnMessage* msg) {
736 // Check mandatory attributes.
737 const StunAddressAttribute* peer_attr =
738 msg->GetAddress(STUN_ATTR_XOR_PEER_ADDRESS);
739 if (!peer_attr) {
740 SendBadRequestResponse(msg);
741 return;
742 }
743
744 if (server_->reject_private_addresses_ &&
745 rtc::IPIsPrivate(peer_attr->GetAddress().ipaddr())) {
746 SendErrorResponse(msg, STUN_ERROR_FORBIDDEN, STUN_ERROR_REASON_FORBIDDEN);
747 return;
748 }
749
750 // Add this permission.
751 AddPermission(peer_attr->GetAddress().ipaddr());
752
753 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Created permission, peer="
754 << peer_attr->GetAddress().ToSensitiveString();
755
756 // Send a success response.
757 TurnMessage response;
758 InitResponse(msg, &response);
759 SendResponse(&response);
760}
761
762void TurnServerAllocation::HandleChannelBindRequest(const TurnMessage* msg) {
763 // Check mandatory attributes.
764 const StunUInt32Attribute* channel_attr =
765 msg->GetUInt32(STUN_ATTR_CHANNEL_NUMBER);
766 const StunAddressAttribute* peer_attr =
767 msg->GetAddress(STUN_ATTR_XOR_PEER_ADDRESS);
768 if (!channel_attr || !peer_attr) {
769 SendBadRequestResponse(msg);
770 return;
771 }
772
773 // Check that channel id is valid.
774 int channel_id = channel_attr->value() >> 16;
775 if (channel_id < kMinChannelNumber || channel_id > kMaxChannelNumber) {
776 SendBadRequestResponse(msg);
777 return;
778 }
779
780 // Check that this channel id isn't bound to another transport address, and
781 // that this transport address isn't bound to another channel id.
782 Channel* channel1 = FindChannel(channel_id);
783 Channel* channel2 = FindChannel(peer_attr->GetAddress());
784 if (channel1 != channel2) {
785 SendBadRequestResponse(msg);
786 return;
787 }
788
789 // Add or refresh this channel.
790 if (!channel1) {
791 channel1 = new Channel(thread_, channel_id, peer_attr->GetAddress());
792 channel1->SignalDestroyed.connect(
793 this, &TurnServerAllocation::OnChannelDestroyed);
794 channels_.push_back(channel1);
795 } else {
796 channel1->Refresh();
797 }
798
799 // Channel binds also refresh permissions.
800 AddPermission(peer_attr->GetAddress().ipaddr());
801
802 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Bound channel, id=" << channel_id
803 << ", peer=" << peer_attr->GetAddress().ToSensitiveString();
804
805 // Send a success response.
806 TurnMessage response;
807 InitResponse(msg, &response);
808 SendResponse(&response);
809}
810
811void TurnServerAllocation::HandleChannelData(const char* data, size_t size) {
812 // Extract the channel number from the data.
813 uint16_t channel_id = rtc::GetBE16(data);
814 Channel* channel = FindChannel(channel_id);
815 if (channel) {
816 // Send the data to the peer address.
817 SendExternal(data + TURN_CHANNEL_HEADER_SIZE,
818 size - TURN_CHANNEL_HEADER_SIZE, channel->peer());
819 } else {
820 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << ToString()
821 << ": Received channel data for invalid channel, id="
822 << channel_id;
823 }
824}
825
826void TurnServerAllocation::OnExternalPacket(
827 rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket,
828 const char* data,
829 size_t size,
830 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr,
831 const int64_t& /* packet_time_us */) {
832 RTC_DCHECK(external_socket_.get() == socket);
833 Channel* channel = FindChannel(addr);
834 if (channel) {
835 // There is a channel bound to this address. Send as a channel message.
836 rtc::ByteBufferWriter buf;
837 buf.WriteUInt16(channel->id());
838 buf.WriteUInt16(static_cast<uint16_t>(size));
839 buf.WriteBytes(data, size);
840 server_->Send(&conn_, buf);
841 } else if (!server_->enable_permission_checks_ ||
842 HasPermission(addr.ipaddr())) {
843 // No channel, but a permission exists. Send as a data indication.
844 TurnMessage msg;
845 msg.SetType(TURN_DATA_INDICATION);
846 msg.SetTransactionID(rtc::CreateRandomString(kStunTransactionIdLength));
847 msg.AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunXorAddressAttribute>(
848 STUN_ATTR_XOR_PEER_ADDRESS, addr));
849 msg.AddAttribute(
850 std::make_unique<StunByteStringAttribute>(STUN_ATTR_DATA, data, size));
851 server_->SendStun(&conn_, &msg);
852 } else {
853 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
854 << ToString() << ": Received external packet without permission, peer="
855 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
856 }
857}
858
859int TurnServerAllocation::ComputeLifetime(const TurnMessage* msg) {
860 // Return the smaller of our default lifetime and the requested lifetime.
861 int lifetime = kDefaultAllocationTimeout / 1000; // convert to seconds
862 const StunUInt32Attribute* lifetime_attr = msg->GetUInt32(STUN_ATTR_LIFETIME);
863 if (lifetime_attr && static_cast<int>(lifetime_attr->value()) < lifetime) {
864 lifetime = static_cast<int>(lifetime_attr->value());
865 }
866 return lifetime;
867}
868
869bool TurnServerAllocation::HasPermission(const rtc::IPAddress& addr) {
870 return (FindPermission(addr) != NULL);
871}
872
873void TurnServerAllocation::AddPermission(const rtc::IPAddress& addr) {
874 Permission* perm = FindPermission(addr);
875 if (!perm) {
876 perm = new Permission(thread_, addr);
877 perm->SignalDestroyed.connect(this,
878 &TurnServerAllocation::OnPermissionDestroyed);
879 perms_.push_back(perm);
880 } else {
881 perm->Refresh();
882 }
883}
884
885TurnServerAllocation::Permission* TurnServerAllocation::FindPermission(
886 const rtc::IPAddress& addr) const {
887 for (PermissionList::const_iterator it = perms_.begin(); it != perms_.end();
888 ++it) {
889 if ((*it)->peer() == addr)
890 return *it;
891 }
892 return NULL;
893}
894
895TurnServerAllocation::Channel* TurnServerAllocation::FindChannel(
896 int channel_id) const {
897 for (ChannelList::const_iterator it = channels_.begin();
898 it != channels_.end(); ++it) {
899 if ((*it)->id() == channel_id)
900 return *it;
901 }
902 return NULL;
903}
904
905TurnServerAllocation::Channel* TurnServerAllocation::FindChannel(
906 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr) const {
907 for (ChannelList::const_iterator it = channels_.begin();
908 it != channels_.end(); ++it) {
909 if ((*it)->peer() == addr)
910 return *it;
911 }
912 return NULL;
913}

915void TurnServerAllocation::SendResponse(TurnMessage* msg) {
916 // Success responses always have M-I.
917 msg->AddMessageIntegrity(key_);
918 server_->SendStun(&conn_, msg);
919}
920
921void TurnServerAllocation::SendBadRequestResponse(const TurnMessage* req) {
922 SendErrorResponse(req, STUN_ERROR_BAD_REQUEST, STUN_ERROR_REASON_BAD_REQUEST);
923}
924
925void TurnServerAllocation::SendErrorResponse(const TurnMessage* req,
926 int code,
927 const std::string& reason) {
928 server_->SendErrorResponse(&conn_, req, code, reason);
929}

931void TurnServerAllocation::SendExternal(const void* data,
932 size_t size,
933 const rtc::SocketAddress& peer) {
934 rtc::PacketOptions options;
935 external_socket_->SendTo(data, size, peer, options);
936}

938void TurnServerAllocation::OnMessage(rtc::Message* msg) {
939 RTC_DCHECK(msg->message_id == MSG_ALLOCATION_TIMEOUT);
940 SignalDestroyed(this);
941 delete this;
942}
943
944void TurnServerAllocation::OnPermissionDestroyed(Permission* perm) {
945 auto it = absl::c_find(perms_, perm);
946 RTC_DCHECK(it != perms_.end());
947 perms_.erase(it);
948}
949
950void TurnServerAllocation::OnChannelDestroyed(Channel* channel) {
951 auto it = absl::c_find(channels_, channel);
952 RTC_DCHECK(it != channels_.end());
953 channels_.erase(it);
954}
